<div class = "home_sliding_box" id = "domainStrategize">
  <div class = "home_text" >
    <div class="closeIt">CLOSE</div>	
    <h1>	Strategise - define direction in an age of uncertainty</h1>
    <div class="col360">
  	  <p>A successful strategy is a robust blend of imagination and coherent intent, a dynamic fit of meaning and context. We work with clients to ignite their inherent creativity and to design their future success by:</p> 
	  <ul>
	    <li>revitalising and harnessing imagination</li>
	    <li>redefining the industry landscape</li>
        <li>recalibrating enterprise systems</li>
	    <li>re-energizing revenue models</li>
	    <li>reinvigorating legacy products and services.</li>
	  </ul>
    </div>
    <div class = "col450">	
	  <p>	We have used the power of story, conversation and design to help leaders:	</p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Rethink their industries and build new pathways into the future</li>
	    <li>Change deeply bureaucratic systems to become more relevant to customers</li>
	    <li>Create compelling value propositions that translate into competitive advantage.</li>
	  </ul>
    </div>	
  </div>

  <div class = "case_study_display">
	<div class = "caseStudy" id = "strategize1_target">
	  <div class="caseStudyClose">CLOSE</div>	
	  <p>A client in the infrastructure industry wanted to make strategic choices about how it positioned itself for the future. It was willing to make bold changes to its business model, or to move into new geographies or new kinds of value offering. But how to be wise about those choices? How to be strategic in the face of a turbulent future where societal trends might open up great possibilities, or close others down entirely?</p>

	  <p>Second Road created an immersive environment for the executive team - a ‘strategy lab’ - helping them to project their image of their business into the industry landscape of the decades to come. It was not a matter of making brittle predictions, but rather of identifying industry, natural and social forces which would inevitably play a part in shaping the environment in which they could play.</p>

      <p>By visualising future possibilities and applying powerful heuristics for choosing strategic options, the executive group set bold direction for their organisation over immediate and long term horizons.</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class = "caseStudy" id = "strategize3_target">
	  <div class="caseStudyClose">CLOSE</div>	
	  <p>A company in the telecommunications industry had set itself a challenging growth target - growth that would need to come from radical strategy. They had identified potentially lucrative new markets, but the current management mindset tended to stick with business as it had been in the past. The company also knew that it faced the challenge of building new capability among its people at the same time as it initiated work to take hold of new opportunities.</p>

	  <p>Second Road helped the company to discover entirely new sources of revenue - unearthing new value in emerging markets. These new directions would also challenge the business to evolve its fundamental business model.</p>

      <p>	We also helped them to frame their propositions in a way that would allow more cautious managers to understand the opportunity and to buy into it as it developed and strengthened. The framework brought together possible new markets, new sectors and new clients, crystallised in new compelling value propositions. The process of strategic innovation helped move managers from ambiguous situation to reliable new business.</p>
	</div>
	
