	  <p>This was the first step on a long and surprising journey with Second Road. Rather than treating students as simply an external stakeholder or customer, we helped them to enter richly into the outlook and experience of their potential customers. A deep identification with the point of view of these crucial users of the education services led the institute to fundamentally rethink its values, objectives and working models. This in turn led to a transformation of its basic stance as a player in the relationships between a new workforce, employers and government.</p>
