    <h1>	Clarify - turn volumes of information into useful knowledge</h1>
    <div class="col360">
	  <p>Your people need to make more informed decisions, faster. To do this, they must:</p> 
	  <ul>	
	    <li>learn to think more clearly</li>
	    <li>demystify complexity</li>
	    <li>extract insights, significance and meaning</li>
	    <li>decipher relevance in data-drenched documents</li>
	    <li>convert information into content that enables good decisions.</li>
	  </ul>
    </div>
    <div class = "col450">	
	  <p>We have used the power of language, conversation and design to help leaders:	</p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Revolutionise reporting to bring focus to essential questions and answers</li>
	    <li>Transform jargon into content that customers understand</li>
	    <li>Bring clarity of intent and meaning to compliance documents.</li>
	  </ul>
    </div>	
  </div>
  <div class = "case_study_display">
	<div class = "caseStudy" id = "clarify1_target">
	  <div class="caseStudyClose">CLOSE</div>	
	  <p>The board of a public company client would regularly receive a risk report, carefully collated from all the activities of five diverse business units. No stone went unturned, or so it would seem - all was bound up in an inch thick document. Unfortunately, the clear and present business-threatening was half way down page 324. And the cluster of risks that weren’t a part of present operations - including regional market shifts and potential pressure from finance bodies - didn’t feature at all. For all its worthy detail, the document was worse than useless for a board member.</p>

	  <p>Second Road worked with the board to ask the right questions of the business. This began a transformation in the way that information was passed between the operation and its governing body. A new genre of document - the Top Down Report™ - became the focus of board conversation. These reports answered all of the key questions on a single page, backed up by detail that a reader could dive into at their leisure and quickly locate the detail they sought.</p>
	</div>
	<div class = "caseStudy" id = "clarify3_target">
	  <div class="caseStudyClose">CLOSE</div>	
	  <p>	A client was involved in a very large infrastructure project for State Government - designing and building a large number of new assets. Progress had ground to a halt, caught in a back and forth game of quibbling about clauses in contract documentation. Engineers would argue the toss about the intention of many design details, with no prospect for actually agreeing to a design specification, let alone a built product.</p>

	  <p>Fundamentally we helped the parties to talk together productively. We created new objects of conversation, centered not on points of contention, but rather on their shared aspiration for designing infrastructure which would serve the community over the decades to come. For the first time, the parties shared a concern for the progress of the project overall, and worked together to advance the design process in record time.</p>
	</div>
	
